00:57:54.810 --> 00:57:56.810
It goes as follows.

00:57:56.810 --> 00:58:00.430
Once testosterone
enters a target cell,

00:58:00.430 --> 00:58:02.760
if this is the scenario
that's going to happen,

00:58:02.760 --> 00:58:05.010
it's inside the cell.

00:58:05.010 --> 00:58:09.930
The testosterone is turned
to estrogen. In other words,

00:58:09.930 --> 00:58:13.110
this weirdo phenomenon has
no effect on circulating

00:58:13.110 --> 00:58:14.180
testosterone levels.

00:58:14.180 --> 00:58:17.790
It's only in target cells
that have the enzyme that

00:58:17.790 --> 00:58:19.040
could do that conversion.

00:58:19.040 --> 00:58:19.540
OK.

00:58:19.540 --> 00:58:22.010
So it's an intracellular
phenomenon.

00:58:22.010 --> 00:58:25.260
If this is leaving you
totally in the dust,

00:58:25.260 --> 00:58:28.460
don't worry about it, except for
a small point coming in awhile.

00:58:28.460 --> 00:58:30.470
But if you want to devote
the rest of your life

00:58:30.470 --> 00:58:32.074
to figuring this
out in more detail,

00:58:32.074 --> 00:58:33.490
there is something
wrong with you.

00:58:33.490 --> 00:58:36.490
But what you've
got here is normal

00:58:36.490 --> 00:58:39.000
circulating levels,
but different effects

00:58:39.000 --> 00:58:40.010
throughout the body.

00:58:40.010 --> 00:58:43.890
In general, what is found is
the effects of testosterone

00:58:43.890 --> 00:58:48.960
in the brain involve this
turning into estrogen,

00:58:48.960 --> 00:58:51.620
as symbolized meaninglessly
by that asterisk.

00:58:51.620 --> 00:58:56.230
Throughout the genitals
or throughout the body,

00:58:56.230 --> 00:58:59.820
and secondary sexual
areas of skin and such,

00:58:59.820 --> 00:59:02.850
testosterone exerts its
effects by being turned

00:59:02.850 --> 00:59:04.670
into dihydrotestosterone.

00:59:04.670 --> 00:59:07.190
And whatever parts are
left over at that point,

00:59:07.190 --> 00:59:09.980
testosterone just does
its regular old thing.

00:59:09.980 --> 00:59:13.960
So this is incredibly
confusing how this can be.

00:59:13.960 --> 00:59:16.690
Immediately, or not so
immediately, two things

00:59:16.690 --> 00:59:17.700
should come to mind.

00:59:17.700 --> 00:59:22.280
OK, so prenatal
testosterone levels

00:59:22.280 --> 00:59:24.650
are going about
their normal prenatal

00:59:24.650 --> 00:59:28.520
organizational masculinization
effects, and part of it

00:59:28.520 --> 00:59:30.520
is on how the brain organizes.

00:59:30.520 --> 00:59:36.150
So what we just saw was prenatal
neurobiological masculinization

00:59:36.150 --> 00:59:39.270
requires testosterone
to be working

00:59:39.270 --> 00:59:43.260
like estrogen in the brain.

00:59:43.260 --> 00:59:47.730
Why don't all the female
fetuses then get androgenized?

00:59:47.730 --> 00:59:50.930
Since they're not generating
estrogen right on site there

00:59:50.930 --> 00:59:53.100
within the cell, but
they're getting estrogen

00:59:53.100 --> 00:59:55.860
through some other route
as their fetal ovaries

00:59:55.860 --> 00:59:56.650
start to work.

00:59:56.650 --> 01:00:00.220
Why isn't mom and her
estrogen androgenizing

01:00:00.220 --> 01:00:02.230
every single fetus out there?

01:00:02.230 --> 01:00:04.970
How is it possible
to ever get a female?

01:00:04.970 --> 01:00:07.590
And the answer to
that is there is

01:00:07.590 --> 01:00:11.370
a protein, which occurs
during pregnancy,

01:00:11.370 --> 01:00:14.050
that occurs in the circulation.

01:00:14.050 --> 01:00:18.240
And what it does is
it binds estrogen,

01:00:18.240 --> 01:00:20.040
and it takes it out of action.

01:00:20.040 --> 01:00:22.476
It leads to estrogen
being degraded.

01:00:22.476 --> 01:00:27.440
In other words, estrogen in
the bloodstream of a fetus

01:00:27.440 --> 01:00:30.970
never has an effect on
any cells in the body.

01:00:30.970 --> 01:00:33.800
Estrogen, whether derived from
the female fetus beginning

01:00:33.800 --> 01:00:37.820
to get her ovaries going there,
or from mom's circulation,

01:00:37.820 --> 01:00:40.120
the estrogen has no effect.

01:00:40.120 --> 01:00:42.710
And in other words,
the only fetuses

01:00:42.710 --> 01:00:45.980
that ever have estrogen
inside their neurons

01:00:45.980 --> 01:00:49.080
are fetuses that are male,
where the estrogen came

01:00:49.080 --> 01:00:51.160
from testosterone.

01:00:51.160 --> 01:00:53.720
So you have to
have this protein,

01:00:53.720 --> 01:00:56.270
and it's something
called alpha fetoprotein.

01:00:56.270 --> 01:00:57.990
It only occurs in fetal life.

01:00:57.990 --> 01:00:59.540
This winds up
being the solution.

01:00:59.540 --> 01:01:02.250
What is implicit
in that, you do not

01:01:02.250 --> 01:01:07.350
get the organizational
feminizing effects of hormones

01:01:07.350 --> 01:01:10.730
prenatally because of
estrogen, because you've just

01:01:10.730 --> 01:01:12.030
guaranteed that doesn't happen.

01:01:12.030 --> 01:01:14.380
You're getting androgenizing
effects that way.

01:01:14.380 --> 01:01:17.100
You don't get prenatal
feminizing effects

01:01:17.100 --> 01:01:20.920
from estrogen. Where does the
brain feminization come from?

01:01:20.920 --> 01:01:23.650
The irritating
