happen much in the real world,

01:27:45.280 --> 01:27:48.510
but what you see for the most
part is that humans are not

01:27:48.510 --> 01:27:51.400
terribly aware of where
somebody is in their cycle.

01:27:51.400 --> 01:27:54.560
Humans have invented
hidden ovulation.

01:27:54.560 --> 01:27:56.380
What's that meant to do?

01:27:56.380 --> 01:27:59.410
Decrease paternity certainty.

01:27:59.410 --> 01:28:02.250
And one argument is
that's a good mechanism

01:28:02.250 --> 01:28:05.590
for decreasing the likelihood
of competitive infanticide.

01:28:05.590 --> 01:28:08.420
The other is it
decreases male attempt

01:28:08.420 --> 01:28:10.620
to control female
sexual behavior,

01:28:10.620 --> 01:28:14.060
because it's less clear when
you need to be doing that.

01:28:14.060 --> 01:28:15.640
So counterstrategies.

01:28:15.640 --> 01:28:19.560
More examples-- this is argued
that in some species that

01:28:19.560 --> 01:28:22.310
have non-reproductive sex
throughout the cycle, that

01:28:22.310 --> 01:28:26.160
is a female counterstrategy
to, again, fool the male when

01:28:26.160 --> 01:28:29.730
ovulation is actually occurring,
increasing the likelihood that

01:28:29.730 --> 01:28:32.680
at such times, she can
get somebody else's genes.

01:28:32.680 --> 01:28:36.300
Other strategies-- we've already
heard about one-- [INAUDIBLE]

01:28:36.300 --> 01:28:38.430
in the competitive
infanticide one, which

01:28:38.430 --> 01:28:42.820
is that whole world of females
that can fake being in estrus,

01:28:42.820 --> 01:28:45.590
that go through pseudo
estrus, all of this

01:28:45.590 --> 01:28:49.390
meant to be ways of keeping
males a little bit less certain

01:28:49.390 --> 01:28:53.320
of when they should be trying
to control female sexual access,

01:28:53.320 --> 01:28:56.800
and thus, she has more
choice in the matter.

01:28:56.800 --> 01:29:00.820
What that brings
us to is thus-- oh,

01:29:00.820 --> 01:29:02.730
