01:30:58.160 --> 01:30:59.220
But it was great.

01:30:59.220 --> 01:31:03.120
You would really wish-- so
now what we have is also

01:31:03.120 --> 01:31:07.610
looking at evolutionary aspects
of female choice in there,

01:31:07.610 --> 01:31:11.660
and in what cases do you get
female-female competition?

01:31:11.660 --> 01:31:14.200
First off, the answer
was obvious in terms

01:31:14.200 --> 01:31:16.980
of looking at traditional
tournament species, which

01:31:16.980 --> 01:31:19.610
is that females have no choice
who they are mating with.

01:31:19.610 --> 01:31:21.550
It's linear access models.

01:31:21.550 --> 01:31:24.160
One female winds up with
the alpha male, two females

01:31:24.160 --> 01:31:26.870
and so on, and this
was the dominant model

01:31:26.870 --> 01:31:30.320
in all of primatology
starting in the '60s.

01:31:30.320 --> 01:31:33.240
And then by around
1980 or so, it

01:31:33.240 --> 01:31:34.960
was recognized that,
in fact, there's

01:31:34.960 --> 01:31:37.810
virtually no evidence
for strict linear access

01:31:37.810 --> 01:31:42.690
models of the main determinant
of who a female mates with is

01:31:42.690 --> 01:31:45.860
who's the winner of male-male
competitive interactions.

01:31:45.860 --> 01:31:48.840
People discovered at the
time that, in fact, there

01:31:48.840 --> 01:31:53.111
was this strange, strange
violation of all these models,

01:31:53.111 --> 01:31:55.610
because it turned out the models
were not based on behavior.

01:31:55.610 --> 01:31:58.220
And this generally was
discovered around that time,

01:31:58.220 --> 01:32:00.420
because that was around
the time that the majority

01:32:00.420 --> 01:32:02.530
of primatologists on
earth suddenly became

01:32:02.530 --> 01:32:05.940
female and started looking
at the female end of things

01:32:05.940 --> 01:32:09.550
and discovered that this
linear access stuff is not,

01:32:09.550 --> 01:32:11.200
in fact, what occurs.

01:32:11.200 --> 01:32:15.630
And out of that came a
completely shocking concept

01:32:15.630 --> 01:32:19.520
that ran through primatology
like a bolt of lightning--

01:32:19.520 --> 01:32:22.300
the notion that there was--
this is the technical term--

01:32:22.300 --> 01:32:25.520
some degree of female choice.

01:32:25.520 --> 01:32:27.470
Oh, whoa.

01:32:27.470 --> 01:32:31.880
That's kind of bizarre,
where females have something

01:32:31.880 --> 01:32:33.220
to do with who they mate with.

01:32:33.220 --> 01:32:35.800
And there's been a whole
world of primatology studies

01:32:35.800 --> 01:32:39.140
since then showing what
female choice is about.

01:32:39.140 --> 01:32:41.700
First off, how
does female choice

01:32:41.700 --> 01:32:44.920
occur in a typical
tournament species?

01:32:44.920 --> 01:32:46.190
You've got this problem.

01:32:46.190 --> 01:32:49.710
With primates, for example,
you wind up with a pair bond,

01:32:49.710 --> 01:32:53.380
with a consortship between a
male and an ovulating female,

01:32:53.380 --> 01:32:55.330
and because it's a
tournament species,

01:32:55.330 --> 01:32:57.850
the male is twice
the size or has

01:32:57.850 --> 01:33:01.570
big huge canines or whatever
stuff he's got there.

01:33:01.570 --> 01:33:04.080
He is physically able
to dominate the female

01:33:04.080 --> 01:33:05.190
quite readily.

01:33:05.190 --> 01:33:08.830
You do not see female choice
in those cases being exerted

01:33:08.830 --> 01:33:10.590
by the female
beating up on the guy

01:33:10.590 --> 01:33:13.050
and her getting to go mate
with who she's interested in.

01:33:13.050 --> 01:33:16.290
What you see is much
more clever behavior

01:33:16.290 --> 01:33:17.900
on the part of the female.

01:33:17.900 --> 01:33:21.120
She will, for example,
exhaust the guy.

01:33:21.120 --> 01:33:23.670
Every time he sits down
to feed, the female

01:33:23.670 --> 01:33:25.060
gets up and starts walking.

01:33:25.060 --> 01:33:28.449
And he has to jump up and
pile together the picnic

01:33:28.449 --> 01:33:29.490
and go running after her.

01:33:29.490 --> 01:33:32.180
Every time he tries to take
a nap, she goes walking.

01:33:32.180 --> 01:33:35.420
Or what you find with baboons
is the most clever thing

01:33:35.420 --> 01:33:39.480
that females do is they go
walk and leave the male right

01:33:39.480 --> 01:33:42.410
in front of his
worst rival, or then

01:33:42.410 --> 01:33:44.480
they'll do it again
and again and again

01:33:44.480 --> 01:33:47.040
and get the guy totally
harried out and crazed,

01:33:47.040 --> 01:33:49.850
and at some point, those
two males will have a fight.

01:33:49.850 --> 01:33:52.750
And what then happens is
she runs off to the bushes

01:33:52.750 --> 01:33:54.430
and has what is
technically called

01:33:54.430 --> 01:33:58.555
a stolen copulation with the guy
she's actually interested in.

01:34:01.060 --> 01:34:04.060
Maybe it's not so bad
to be a female baboon.

01:34:04.060 --> 01:34:06.510
So now what this
brings us to insofar

01:34:06.510 --> 01:34:10.140
as this alternative female
strategy is available,

01:34:10.140 --> 01:34:13.380
we now come to this
absolutely critical question,

01:34:13.380 --> 01:34:15.590
one that is run through
the ages, which is,

01:34:15.590 --> 01:34:18.300
what do female baboons want?

01:34:18.300 --> 01:34:19.850
Who do they want to mate with?

01:34:19.850 --> 01:34:23.260
And people are not
positive, but there

01:34:23.260 --> 01:34:25.690
is some suggestion in the data.

01:34:25.690 --> 01:34:27.500
It needs to be replicated more.

01:34:27.500 --> 01:34:30.360
There is this trend, but
there's this suggestion

01:34:30.360 --> 01:34:34.420
that female baboons like to
mate with male baboons, who

01:34:34.420 --> 01:34:36.680
are nice to them.

01:34:36.680 --> 01:34:38.130
No, are they sure?

01:34:38.130 --> 01:34:38.900
Are they certain?

01:34:38.900 --> 01:34:41.180
Have they done their
statistics right?

01:34:41.180 --> 01:34:45.480
They go, and they mate with
guys who groom them a lot,

01:34:45.480 --> 01:34:47.430
guys who play with
their infants,

01:34:47.430 --> 01:34:50.060
guys who, when they're in a
bad mood, don't beat up on them

01:34:50.060 --> 01:34:51.570
but beat up on somebody else.

01:34:51.570 --> 01:34:54.200
This counts as a prince
of the male baboon.

01:34:54.200 --> 01:34:56.170
This is someone you
take home to meet mom.

01:34:56.170 --> 01:34:59.280
When he's in a bad mood, he
pummels someone else, not me.

01:34:59.280 --> 01:35:02.040
This is someone you
want to mate with.

01:35:02.040 --> 01:35:05.710
And in the mid 1980s, excellent
primatologist Barbara Smuts

01:35:05.710 --> 01:35:07.550
of University of
Michigan came up

01:35:07.550 --> 01:35:10.130
with the very jargony
scientific term

01:35:10.130 --> 01:35:11.900
that all sorts of
non-human primates

01:35:11.900 --> 01:35:14.110
have intersexual friendships.

01:35:14.110 --> 01:35:17.240
And that's not an
anthropomorphic term.

01:35:17.240 --> 01:35:19.050
What it was though
was people sort

01:35:19.050 --> 01:35:21.840
of snickering at it in
that the initial notion was

01:35:21.840 --> 01:35:23.720
that these were just friends.

01:35:23.720 --> 01:35:26.290
These were platonic
monkey relationships.

01:35:26.290 --> 01:35:27.930
They were not
about reproduction,

01:35:27.930 --> 01:35:30.880
and it was not until people
got good enough and enough data

01:35:30.880 --> 01:35:33.640
to start picking up on all
those stolen copulations

01:35:33.640 --> 01:35:35.860
to see that the
females were picking up

01:35:35.860 --> 01:35:38.907
and mating with their nice
guy-- oh, we're just friends.

01:35:38.907 --> 01:35:40.990
I could never see him--
whoa, and they're suddenly

01:35:40.990 --> 01:35:42.140
in the bushes with him.

01:35:42.140 --> 01:35:46.067
And it suddenly turned from the,
yeah, nice guys finish last.

01:35:46.067 --> 01:35:48.400
OK, they do lots of grooming,
but let's count the number

01:35:48.400 --> 01:35:50.800
of copies of genes,
to becoming apparent

01:35:50.800 --> 01:35:55.540
that the being a nice guy was a
viable alternative reproductive

01:35:55.540 --> 01:35:59.390
strategy as long as there was
this thing of female choice.

01:35:59.390 --> 01:36:01.770
And what the paternity
studies began to show

01:36:01.770 --> 01:36:05.970
was that was a very viable
alternative strategy, in part,

01:36:05.970 --> 01:36:07.950
because you're not
mating anywhere near as

01:36:07.950 --> 01:36:11.300
much if you were a low
ranking affiliative male.

01:36:11.300 --> 01:36:14.320
With a female, you're not
mating anywhere near as much

01:36:14.320 --> 01:36:17.860
as the high ranking males,
but you're not burning out.

01:36:17.860 --> 01:36:19.030
You're not getting injured.

01:36:19.030 --> 01:36:20.970
You're not having the
male-male fighting.

01:36:20.970 --> 01:36:24.900
You live a lot longer,
and this keeps happening.

01:36:24.900 --> 01:36:27.260
There's a problem,
though, which is

01:36:27.260 --> 01:36:30.410
suppose you are a
female baboon, and you

01:36:30.410 --> 01:36:32.284
want to mate with
this nice guy, and one

01:36:32.284 --> 01:36:33.700
of the things that
he's nice about

01:36:33.700 --> 01:36:35.340
is he's nice to
your kid, who's now

01:36:35.340 --> 01:36:37.380
about three or four years old.

01:36:37.380 --> 01:36:39.137
And there's a very
good chance that where

01:36:39.137 --> 01:36:41.000
that affiliative
relationship started

01:36:41.000 --> 01:36:43.640
with him got jump started was
the fact that he was the most

01:36:43.640 --> 01:36:47.170
likely father of that kid
and has developed somewhat

01:36:47.170 --> 01:36:48.972
of an affiliative
relationship with the kid

01:36:48.972 --> 01:36:50.930
and hangs out with them
and hangs out with you.

01:36:50.930 --> 01:36:52.490
And so you've
established this is

01:36:52.490 --> 01:36:54.270
a nice guy I want to mate with.

01:36:54.270 --> 01:36:56.660
But there's a problem,
which was if he

01:36:56.660 --> 01:36:58.410
was the likely
father of your now

01:36:58.410 --> 01:37:00.900
three, four-year-old
offspring, the odds

01:37:00.900 --> 01:37:02.830
are that three,
four years ago, he

01:37:02.830 --> 01:37:05.440
was a pretty high ranking male.

01:37:05.440 --> 01:37:07.750
And what that means now
three, four years later

01:37:07.750 --> 01:37:11.890
is he's likely to be some
aging guy over the hill, whose

01:37:11.890 --> 01:37:13.600
rank has been dropping.

01:37:13.600 --> 01:37:15.690
In other words,
not someone who is

01:37:15.690 --> 01:37:18.640
going to be very effective
at male-male competition,

01:37:18.640 --> 01:37:21.920
and you get this
horrible sort of tension

01:37:21.920 --> 01:37:25.140
there going on between the
male-male competitive world

01:37:25.140 --> 01:37:28.204
generates some Arnold
Schwarzenegger jerk,

01:37:28.204 --> 01:37:30.620
who's the one who's supposed
to be where she wants to mate

01:37:30.620 --> 01:37:32.650
with Alan Alda or whoever.

01:37:32.650 --> 01:37:35.080
And what you have
then is he's not

01:37:35.080 --> 01:37:37.210
up to the male-male
competitive stuff,

01:37:37.210 --> 01:37:38.940
because he's some aging guy.

01:37:38.940 --> 01:37:43.410
And you instead have the
world of stolen copulations.

01:37:43.410 --> 01:37:44.790
So isn't that great?

01:37:44.790 --> 01:37:45.990
Isn't that heartwarming?

01:37:45.990 --> 01:37:49.850
A whole world of what are now
called alternative strategies.

01:37:49.850 --> 01:37:52.780
If you're some scheming
male baboon wanting

01:37:52.780 --> 01:37:55.000
to pass on as many
copies of your genes,

01:37:55.000 --> 01:37:57.560
you may decide the
really manipulative thing

01:37:57.560 --> 01:37:59.990
to do is to be
nice to some female

01:37:59.990 --> 01:38:02.780
and groom her more
than she grooms

01:38:02.780 --> 01:38:05.780
you, which is a very rare
thing for a male baboon to do.

01:38:05.780 --> 01:38:10.250
So great alternative
strategies, very heartwarming.

01:38:10.250 --> 01:38:12.910
Not so heartwarming,
because there

01:38:12.910 --> 01:38:17.370
are other alternative strategies
available in some species,

01:38:17.370 --> 01:38:21.010
alternatives where male
sexual behavior is not

01:38:21.010 --> 01:38:24.130
the outcome of explicit
male-male competition,

01:38:24.130 --> 01:38:26.680
but instead takes an
alternative strategy.

01:38:26.680 --> 01:38:30.940
And you see one example
of this in orangutans.

01:38:30.940 --> 01:38:33.460
Orangutans, great
apes, and they've

01:38:33.460 --> 01:38:36.710
got a very interesting bizarre
social system, but what

01:38:36.710 --> 01:38:39.920
you have is your basic,
nonetheless, sort of familiar

01:38:39.920 --> 01:38:43.870
picture of male-male competition
with a large percentage

01:38:43.870 --> 01:38:45.680
of orangutan male
aggressions built

01:38:45.680 --> 01:38:47.780
around the reproductive
access to females,

01:38:47.780 --> 01:38:50.730
and you've got a whole
world of very peripheralized

01:38:50.730 --> 01:38:53.499
low ranking males
who never mate.

01:38:53.499 --> 01:38:55.040
And there's an
interesting physiology

01:38:55.040 --> 01:38:56.420
that goes along with it.

01:38:56.420 --> 01:38:59.090
That was the picture that
everybody used to have,

01:38:59.090 --> 01:39:02.980
and then in the 1970s, pioneer
researcher in this, Birute

01:39:02.980 --> 01:39:06.310
Galdikas, who has studied
orangs for decades

01:39:06.310 --> 01:39:09.110
out there in Indonesia,
she noted something

01:39:09.110 --> 01:39:12.550
really disturbing,
which is low ranking,

01:39:12.550 --> 01:39:16.290
non-reproductive male orangs
have an alternative mating

01:39:16.290 --> 01:39:17.110
strategy.

01:39:17.110 --> 01:39:18.220
What do they do?

01:39:18.220 --> 01:39:21.880
They rape females, and this
was the first introduction

01:39:21.880 --> 01:39:24.610
of that term into
zoology, and that is not

01:39:24.610 --> 01:39:26.050
an anthropomorphism.

01:39:26.050 --> 01:39:30.270
If defined as a violent
process of mating

01:39:30.270 --> 01:39:32.450
with a female against
her will, this

01:39:32.450 --> 01:39:34.540
is what goes on in orangutans.

01:39:34.540 --> 01:39:36.960
A certain percentage
of reproduction

01:39:36.960 --> 01:39:40.190
is low ranking guys who
have no direct access

01:39:40.190 --> 01:39:43.110
to females as a result of
male-male interactions.

01:39:43.110 --> 01:39:45.580
This is not the nice
guy alternative,

01:39:45.580 --> 01:39:47.730
so there is precedent
for this also.

01:39:47.730 --> 01:39:50.790
And this is by now very
well-documented behavior

01:39:50.790 --> 01:39:52.820
among orangutans.

01:39:52.820 --> 01:39:54.680
Then if you want to
call it with something

01:39:54.680 --> 01:39:57.390
very subtle and clever,
there's apparently

01:39:57.390 --> 01:39:59.720
this whole world
of fish species,

01:39:59.720 --> 01:40:02.840
where low ranking males
can pretend to be a female

01:40:02.840 --> 01:40:06.090
and take on female coloration
and pretend to be just

01:40:06.090 --> 01:40:08.342
friends and someone they
can pour their heart out to,

01:40:08.342 --> 01:40:10.175
and then suddenly one
day they have a penis,

01:40:10.175 --> 01:40:11.790
and where'd that come from?

01:40:11.790 --> 01:40:13.871
And everything
suddenly changes there.

01:40:13.871 --> 01:40:14.370
OK.

01:40:14.370 --> 01:40:17.170
So we have the very
strict boring models.

01:40:17.170 --> 01:40:19.630
Females invest more
calories than males,

01:40:19.630 --> 01:40:21.600
and, thus, they are
much more picky.

01:40:21.600 --> 01:40:24.050
Males mate with females
entirely as a function

01:40:24.050 --> 01:40:26.190
of male-male competition,
and thus, evolution

01:40:26.190 --> 01:40:29.720
is driven by male
aggression and all of that.

01:40:29.720 --> 01:40:32.070
Let me just see as
people are clearly

01:40:32.070 --> 01:40:33.548
about to run out the door.

01:40:36.340 --> 01:40:39.750
For more, please visit
us at stanford.edu.

